{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8ff39a28-1e01-4ac9-9775-5a403501e37e","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"DisplayName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7ca5905c-8777-4d8a-95bf-be3631b0e960","outputTokens":166},"id":"496ac5d7-78f0-4b3e-8cc7-4cc250aaf907","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:56:51.125Z","parentId":"e38f76cb-13ad-44d1-88ff-471c6f95735b"}
